
[1]sanguinary

   SAN'GUINARY, a. [L. sanguinarius, from sanguis, blood.]

   1. Bloody; attended with much bloodshed; murderous; as a sanguinary
   war, contest or battle.

   2. Blood thirsty; cruel; eager to shed blood.

   Passion - makes us brutal and sanguinary.

                          SAN'GUINARY, n. A plant.
